-   [#​1565](https://redirect.github.com/lint-staged/lint-staged/pull/1565) [`3686977`](https://redirect.github.com/lint-staged/lint-staged/commit/3686977ccdadf70b709c16c0346ef6c2b18e2376) Thanks [@​iiroj](https://redirect.github.com/iiroj)! - *Lint-staged* now explicitly warns about potential data loss when using `--no-stash`.

-   [#​1558](https://redirect.github.com/lint-staged/lint-staged/pull/1558) [`c37dc38`](https://redirect.github.com/lint-staged/lint-staged/commit/c37dc38dddbdebc41df4dbd909d79c98c3f69eb3) Thanks [@​iiroj](https://redirect.github.com/iiroj)! - The minimum required Node.js version is lowered to `20.17` following [nano-spawn@1.0.2](https://redirect.github.com/sindresorhus/nano-spawn/releases/tag/v1.0.2).

Change-Id: I66e7b4e8a12e06eb98e4d4dd9c35a5c42f2d6347
Signed-off-by: Ashod Nakashian <ashod.nakashian@collabora.co.uk>

wsd: test: fix race in UnitWOPILoadEncoded

This race causes the test to be flagged
as finished, which results in short-cutting
UnitWSD::get().handleHttpRequest().

This in turn changes the control flow in
ClientRequestDispatcher::handleMessage().

This doesn't have any observable side-effects,
except that unintended code gets executed.

The race condition fixed makes the test
flow controlled and the code executed
the one expected and intended.

Change-Id: Iede90b9cfbdfc4fa1bea4b4236b3776810abed71
Signed-off-by: Ashod Nakashian <ashod.nakashian@collabora.co.uk>

wsd: test: make DeleteAll faster

A 'textselection:' message is always
emmitted upon loading a document, this
is confused with the one expected from
uno:SelectAll, which we issued right
after loading a document. This made
us issue uno:Delete too soon, which
put us out of sync with the events
published by core. End result: the
test took over 250 seconds to finish.

We now drain the initial 'textselection:'
message before issuing uno:SelectAll and
the same test now takes around 200 ms!

Signed-off-by: Ashod Nakashian <ashod.nakashian@collabora.co.uk>

wsd: test: convert cerr output to proper logging

We can still output the log to the console,
if so we wish, but at least the cerr entries
are now consistent with the general logging
and we can easily see timestamps, thread-id,
and other meta-data.

Change-Id: I8a314b4d89a39e5e1a0534b99c288d22a9a2d536
Signed-off-by: Ashod Nakashian <ashod.nakashian@collabora.co.uk>

wsd: test: support replaying with a custom latency-factor

Replayed commands by default take as long as
the original recording took. This can be
unnecessarily slow, given that human input
takes in the order of 100s of milliseconds,
if not seconds.

We now support replaying with a custom
latency-factor, which allows for speeding
up or slowing down the replacy.

By using a factor of 0.1, we can run
Unit-Perf about 10x faster (~13 seconds
instead of ~120 seconds).

Change-Id: Ic75eb316e92302d54480506ff09efe23c8388e70
Signed-off-by: Ashod Nakashian <ashod.nakashian@collabora.co.uk>

make: reorder tests to improve parallelism

slow tests first, to improve placement.
